examples.en: Jim intends to go after the big prize.
Have you heard the story that she intends to resign?
She has issued a statement that she intends to be a candidate.
His ex-wife clearly intends to bleed him for every last penny.
The Government intends to award an order to the small business.
He intends to oppose the prime minister in the leadership election.
The government intends to institute court action against such firms.
Dr Hayward intends to raise the museum's profile (=make it more well-known).
She intends to chronicle the broad social changes that have occurred in this part of the country.
As to our future plans, I think I need only say that the company intends to expand at a steady rate.
